  "response": "The Adidas cotton deodorant was discontinued for a variety of reasons that could include changes in consumer preferences, market demand, or strategic shifts by Adidas within their product lineup. While official statements from the company might not detail specific reasons for discontinuation, companies often reassess product lines to optimize their offerings based on sales performance and customer feedback.\n\nAs for customer opinions, while some may have enjoyed the cotton deodorant for its scent or effectiveness, others might have preferred different formulations or found it did not meet their expectations. Generally, consumer reviews often highlight effectiveness, scent preference, skin sensitivity, and longevity as key factors in their evaluations of such products.\n\nIf you are looking for specific customer feedback or reviews, various consumer opinion sites or forums might provide a more comprehensive view of what users thought about the product before its discontinuation.",
